(a) the functional and structural form of the estimation method; 
(b) assumptions on which the estimation method is based; 
(c) the cyclicality of the estimation method; 
(d) the length of the historical observation period used in accordance with Article 
45; 
(e) the margin of conservatism applied in accordance with Article 44; 
(f) the human judgement; 
(g) where applicable, the choice of risk drivers.

